      • Serialized Fields

        • epsilon

          double epsilon
          The epsilon used for coordinate comparisons. Defines the maximum absolute difference at which coordinates should be considered equal. Zero indicates that exact coordinate comparisons should be used.

          Note: List.sort(java.util.Comparator<? super E>) throws IllegalArgumentException when supplied a PointDComparator whose PointDComparator.epsilon overlaps the coordinates of distinct PointD instances in both dimensions, resulting in the classification of PointD instances as equal when their PointD.equals(org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, org.kynosarges.tektosyne.geometry.PointD, double) and PointD.hashCode() results signal inequality. ("Comparison method violates its general contract.")
